author: johnh
msg: Slight refactor of DefaultIframeUriManager affording more flexibility in when to add a security token to a rendering URI.
Also, uses concrete (non-templatized) token if such token is provided.

author: dannas
msg: Fix bug in the diff parser where only the first property hunk after
a property header was detected.
* subversion/libsvn_diff/parse-diff.c
(parse_next_hunk): Introduce a new out parameter 'is_property' for
determerning the type of the returned hunk.
(svn_diff_parse_next_patch): Store the last prop name we've parsed
to be able to identify what property a hunk belongs to.
* subversion/tests/libsvn_diff/parse-diff-test.c
(property_unidiff): Use two hunks for one property.
(test_parse_property_diff): Check two hunks for one property.

author: dannas
msg: Use a hash table instead of an array for storing property patches. Makes it
easier to insert new hunks.
* subversion/include/svn_diff.h
(svn_patch_t): Use a hash table for storing property patches.
* subversion/libsvn_diff/parse-diff.c
(add_property_hunk
svn_diff_parse_next_patch): Update callers to use apr_hash_* funcs.
* subversion/tests/libsvn_diff/parse-diff-test.c
(test_parse_property_diff,
test_parse_property_and_text_diff): Update callers to use apr_hash_*
funcs
